data.title: Janet Jackson
data.text:
AKA Janet Damita Jo Jackson

Born: 16-May-1966

Birthplace: Gary, IN

Gender: Female

Race or Ethnicity: Black

Sexual orientation: Straight

Occupation: Singer, Actor

Nationality: United States

Executive summary: What Have You Done For Me Lately?

"My first crush was on Barry Manilow. He performed on television, and I remember taping it. When no one was around, I used to kiss the screen."

Father: Joe Jackson (b. 26-Jul-1929)

Mother: Katherine Jackson (b. 4-May-1930)

Sister: Rebbie Jackson ("Maureen", b. 29-May-1950)

Brother: Jackie Jackson (b. 4-May-1951)

Brother: Tito Jackson (b. 15-Oct-1953)

Brother: Jermaine Jackson (b. 11-Dec-1954)

Sister: La Toya Jackson (b. 29-May-1956)

Brother: Marlon Jackson (b. 12-Mar-1957)

Brother: Randy Jackson (b. 29-Oct-1961)

Brother: Michael Jackson (b. 29-Aug-1958, d. 25-Jun-2009)

Husband: James DeBarge (m. Aug-1984, div. Mar-1985, annulled)

Husband: Rene Elizondo (b. 16-Jul-1962, dating 1985, m. 31-Mar-1991, div. 13-Mar-2000)

Boyfriend: Jermaine Dupri (music producer, together 2001-08, broken engagement)

Husband: Wissam Al Mana (billionaire, m. 2012)

High School: Montclair Prep, Van Nuys, CA

Endorsement of McDonald's

Hollywood Walk of Fame 1500 Vine Street (recordings)

Defamation according to lawsuit filed by music producer Eric Christian (12-Jun-2002)

Abortion 1984

Visited Disneyland Captain EO premiere (Sep-1986)

Funeral: Michael Jackson (2009)
